Namaste,

I heard in one Youtube videos recently that one can attain enlightenment just by sweeping floors. This got me thinking. I also read somewhere that you should acquire one pointedness in your thoughts(as in no conflicting thoughts - is what I understood).

I usually listen to these satsang videos when I am doing household chores. For example, when I am cooking I am not 100% cooking, but in fact listening to these videos. Cooking happens mechanically. When I am driving, I am also chanting something or other. Emphasis of course is more on driving, chanting happens mechanically. 
Now I am wondering if this is a good practice, or indeed I should (try to) pay full attention to what I'm doing on hand?

Thanks,
Sushma
